{"type":"message","id":"802eb9c3","parentId":"cd44b276","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:58:18.679Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_55j3gcxl78gu_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 045714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. Key pending item: \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\" - Implement Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier on pulse logs\r\n3. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe insight from this session is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The next logical step is to implement the TIC experiment on the existing pulse logs.\r\n\r\nI should look at what files exist and implement the TIC classifier. Let me check the pulse logs and implement this experiment.\r\n\r\nFirst, let me observe the pulse_*.md files in the logs directory and understand their structure, then implement a TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nGiven I'm a stateless agent, I need to:\r\n1. Read existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier that can identify invariants vs variants\r\n3. Test it against the success criteria\r\n\r\nLet me implement the TIC experiment script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_classifier.py` - a script that reads recent pulse logs, identifies invariant (stable) vs variant (changing) content patterns, and measures classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction success against the defined criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\nTests the hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nIdentifies invariants across pulse logs and validates:\r\n- Classification accuracy: >70% invariant/variant\r\n- Next-pulse prediction: >60% accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef parse_pulse(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key-value sections from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = filepath.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract observation, action, mutation sections\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    act_match = re.search(r\"### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    mut_match = re.search(r\"### MUTATION\\s*\\n```\\s*\\n(.*?)\\n```\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"file\": str(filepath),\r\n        \"timestamp\": filepath.stem,\r\n        \"observation\": obs_match.group(1).strip() if obs_match else \"\",\r\n        \"action\": act_match.group(1).strip() if act_match else \"\",\r\n        \"mutation\": mut_match.group(1).strip() if mut_match else \"(no mutation)\"\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariant_tokens(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Extract tokens that appear across multiple pulses (invariants)\r\n    vs tokens that appear rarely (variants).\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    all_tokens = Counter()\r\n    pulse_tokens = []\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        # Tokenize key content areas\r\n        text = f\"{pulse['observation']} {pulse['action']}\"\r\n        tokens = set(re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_]{3,}\\b', text.lower()))\r\n        all_tokens.update(tokens)\r\n        pulse_tokens.append(tokens)\r\n    \r\n    # Define threshold: tokens in >60% of pulses are invariants\r\n    threshold = len(pulses) * 0.6\r\n    invariants = {t for t, c in all_tokens.items() if c >= threshold}\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, all_tokens\r\n\r\ndef classify_pulse(pulse, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant-heavy or variant-heavy.\"\"\"\r\n    text = f\"{pulse['observation']} {pulse['action']}\"\r\n    tokens = set(re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_]{3,}\\b', text.lower()))\r\n    \r\n    if not tokens:\r\n        return \"unknown\", 0.0\r\n    \r\n    invariant_count = len(tokens & invariants)\r\n    ratio = invariant_count / len(tokens)\r\n    \r\n    # Classification: ratio > 0.3 = invariant, else variant\r\n    return \"invariant\" if ratio > 0.3 else \"variant\", ratio\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(current, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse will be invariant-heavy or variant-heavy.\"\"\"\r\n    _, ratio = classify_pulse(current, invariants)\r\n    # Simple heuristic: if current is invariant-heavy, next likely similar\r\n    return \"invariant\" if ratio > 0.3 else \"variant\"\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    # Collect pulse logs\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=lambda f: f.name)\r\n    pulses = [parse_pulse(f) for f in pulse_files if f.stat().st_size > 100]\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulses) < 5:\r\n        print(f\"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulses, found {len(pulses)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Use first 80% for training, last 20% for testing\r\n    split = int(len(pulses) * 0.8)\r\n    train_pulses = pulses[:split]\r\n    test_pulses = pulses[split:]\r\n    \r\n    # Extract invariants from training set\r\n    invariants, token_counts = extract_invariant_tokens(train_pulses)\r\n    \r\n   \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:57:44\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774342698678}}
